  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency WaSH Assistance to Flood Affected Families of Rautahat District</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Following consultation with the affected population, Christian Aid in partnership with Aasaman Nepal, will provide Wash support to 800 HHs, including access to safe drinking water and suppot for imporved hygiene and sanitation. This will include:
- Disinfection of contaminated water sources via chlorination of handumps
- Distribution of hygiene/ dignity kits
- Hygiene promotion
- installation of communal latrines with handwashing facilities and bathing spaces</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed actions are aimed at bringing immediate relief to flood - affected families. This will directly help alleviate suffering and maintain the dignity of those affected by the disaster and fill critical gaps in the ongoing humanitarain response. The provision to access safe drinking water through chlorination of handpumps , the construction of temporary latrines and bathing spaes, ditribution of hygiene kits and provision of hygiene promotion will all contribute to preventing outbreak and spread of water borne diseases.</narrative>
  </description>
